Rating: 4
I have made this salad twice, and each time enjoyed it thoroughly. It's simple to make; it's different from the usual potato salad; and, most importantly, it tastes great. I have to disagree with those reviewers who say the salad is bland or needs additional seasoning. Sometimes you can over-complicate a recipe to the point you really cannot savor the principal ingredients. This is a chive aioli potato and pea salad -- each of these four ingredients "speaks out" in this recipe, meaning that you can taste the potatoes, the peas, the chives and the garlic. If you can make the salad well in advance of serving, the chives, in particular, have a chance to assert themselves. I did cook my peas, cooled them in cold water, and drained and dried them before putting them in the salad.

