I make a similar salad (my non-potato salad eating husband requests it!) I cube redskin potatoes, and boil, then rinse in cold. Add frozen peas and corn (fresh will be great when available). I dress with mayo, combined with chopped garlic and an assortment of chopped herbs (whatever strikes me as good in the garden that day). I don't measure, but it's probably a cup of mayo with 2-3 large garlic cloves and 1/4 cup or so of herbs, chopped. Salt and pepper to taste.

